  "prompt": "English Grammar: Which is more Grammatically Correct - \"I wish I was there\" OR \"I wish I were there\"?",
  "response": "The more grammatically correct form is \"I wish I were there.\" This construction uses the subjunctive mood, which is used to express hypothetical or contrary-to-fact situations. While \"I wish I was there\" is commonly used in informal speech, \"I wish I were there\" is traditionally considered more grammatically accurate.",
